  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "A lensing mass pushes the surface up at nearby locations.",
    "If the lensing mass profile is circular and directly in front of the source, the minimum of the parabola will be replaced by a hill with a circular valley around it.",
    "However, unless the lens is perfectly circular and the source is perfectly centered behind it, the valley will not be perfectly symmetric, but will have a bowl on one side.",
    "Elongated mass distributions can lead to two bowls, and for more complicated mass distributions, further minima and maxima may appear.",
    "Each bowl and hill corresponds to an image location, because, by definition, ∇τ (θ) = 0 at minima and maxima."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}